{{Quote|Careful, human. ''[&hellip;]'' Be very careful. I don't know what schostri stings would do to a human, but they're quickly fatal to most other life-forms we've used them against.|General Bearsh, to Dean Jinzler|<ref name="SQ">''[[Survivor's Quest]]''</ref>}}
The '''Schostri''' were a [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Insect/Legends|insects]] similar to [[wasp]]s that were armed with stings. The [[Vagaari/Legends|Vagaari]] species utilized the schostri in combat situations, storing them within holed gauntlets under their [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]]. Once the insects perceived the adrenaline of their Vagaari host, they formed swarms, capable of stinging their enemies a dozen times and [[Death/Legends|killing]] almost every [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]], and<ref name="TUR">''[[The Unknown Regions]]''</ref> encircled the Vagaari.<ref name="SQ" /> The [[Vagaari Empire]]'s high&ndash;ranking members also used the insects' expensive to manufacture [[Schostri toxin|toxin]] to create an airborne poison that could eliminate everyone, even its user, within a twenty&ndash;[[Meter/Legends|meter]] radius.<ref name="TUR" />

